ASABA – Delta State House of Assembly Aspirant for Ethiope-West Constituency, Edafe Ofotokun, on Wednesday tipped Governor Ifeanyi Okowa for a higher political office in 2023. Speaking on Wednesday at the PDP Secretariat, Asaba, Ofotokun promised to give his constituents efficient representation if given the mandate. According to him, “I aspire to serve the people of Ethiope- West Constituency at the Delta State House of Assembly. If given the opportunity to serve, I would ensure purposeful representation and people-oriented programmes. “The youths will be coordinated through a self-sustaining programme of entrepreneurship and the women will be grouped into cells of business support to exchange ideas and access business support stipends,” he promised. He expressed optimism over the chances to retain power by providing the next governor of the state as he prayed for wisdom for Governor Senator Ifeanyi Okowa, leader of the party, James Ibori and other stakeholders of the party for a peaceful and smooth transition of powers in 2023. He further mentioned that the Governor Okowa has the capacity for a higher elective office, saying that he can positively affect the lives of Nigerians.